  "text": "Apache Kafka enforces log retention policies through a comprehensive set of Java components. The configuration definitions for log.retention.ms and log.retention.bytes are declared in TopicConfig.java (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/config/TopicConfig.java) which defines RETENTION_MS_CONFIG and RETENTION_BYTES_CONFIG, and ServerLogConfigs.java (server-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/config/ServerLogConfigs.java) which provides broker-level retention configuration.\n\nThe core retention policy validation occurs in LogConfig.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogConfig.java), which contains multiple validation methods: validateBrokerLogConfigValues() validates broker-level retention configurations, validateRemoteStorageRetentionSize() ensures local retention bytes are not greater than overall retention bytes when remote storage is enabled, validateRemoteStorageRetentionTime() ensures local retention milliseconds do not exceed overall retention milliseconds, and validateRetentionConfigsWhenRemoteCopyDisabled() validates that local and global retention values match when remote copy is disabled. The configuration class also provides getter methods localRetentionMs() and localRetentionBytes() that properly handle both local and global retention settings.\n\nThe actual segment deletion enforcement for both time-based and size-based retention is implemented in UnifiedLog.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/UnifiedLog.java). The deleteOldSegments() method orchestrates the deletion process by calling deleteRetentionMsBreachedSegments() for time-based retention (which checks if the time elapsed since the segment's largest timestamp exceeds retentionMs) and deleteRetentionSizeBreachedSegments() for size-based retention (which deletes segments when the log size exceeds retentionSize). The deleteSegments() method performs the actual segment deletion. Two static helper methods, localRetentionMs() and localRetentionSize(), calculate the effective retention values based on whether remote log storage is enabled and configured.\n\nFor local segment file deletion, LocalLog.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LocalLog.java) provides the deleteSegmentFiles() method which handles the physical deletion of segment files with optional async deletion support.\n\nFor remote log tiered storage, RemoteLogManager.java (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/log/remote/storage/RemoteLogManager.java) implements retention enforcement through its inner class RemoteLogRetentionHandler, which checks segment deletion conditions based on retention size (isSegmentBreachedBySize()), retention time (isSegmentBreachedByTime()), and log start offset. The manager builds retention data structures using buildRetentionTimeData() and buildRetentionSizeData() methods to determine which remote segments should be deleted."
}

